5 x 2 is the same as 5 groups of 2 or 2 groups of 5. So 5 x 2 = 5 + 5 = 10. Therefore, 5 x 2 = 10.
7 x 8 is the same as 7 groups of 8 or 8 groups of 7. So 7 x 8 = 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 = 56. Therefore, 7 x 8 = 56.
12 x 6 is the same as 12 groups of 6 or 6 groups of 12. So 12 x 6 = 12 + 12 + 12 + 12 + 12 + 12 = 72. Therefore, 12 x 6 = 72.
22 ÷ 11 is the same as finding how many groups of 11 are in 22. Since 22 can be split into 2 groups of 11, 22 ÷ 11 = 2.
39 ÷ 3 is the same as finding how many groups of 3 are in 39. Since 39 can be split into 13 groups of 3, 39 ÷ 3 = 13.
84 ÷ 4 is the same as finding how many groups of 4 are in 84. Since 84 can be split into 21 groups of 4, 84 ÷ 4 = 21.
